column36: Clear second at Sedgefield recently and reappears before a 6lb rise kicks in
column37: Having been sent off favourite he returned to form with a clear second at Sedgefield ten days ago (2m1f, soft; won the same race 12 months previously); reappears before a 6lb rise kicks in and he's a leading contender.

column36: Easy win at Ludlow last Monday and he's a big player again under a penalty
column37: Triple Flat winner who made it ninth-time lucky over hurdles when justifying favouritism at Ludlow (2m) last Monday; that was an easy win under under Harry Cobden and he's strongly respected under a penalty in his follow-up bid; last success was on good ground but two of his Flat wins came in the mud.
